Laboratory methods for early detection of human immunodeficiency virus type 1 in newborns and infants. Cumulative data on serological testing of newborns and infants have shown that (i) maternal and newborn anti-HIV-1 IgG titers are high at delivery, which may explain the persistence of antibody in the infants of seropositive mothers (ii) in some situations, serial HIV-1 antibody testing may identify infected infants